Units: 312
Acres: +/-25
Extension of Inspection Period: Purchaser shall have the option to extend the Initial Inspection Period for two sixty (60) day periods upon the following terms: (i) Purchaser must deliver written notice of the first such extension to Seller prior to the expiration of the Initial Inspection Period, and notice of the second such extension to Seller prior to the expiration of the first Extension Period, and (ii) Purchaser must deposit additional earnest money with Escrow Agent in the amount of Twenty Five Thousand and No/100 Dollars ($25,000.00) (the Additional Deposits), prior to the commencement of each Extension Period. The Additional Deposit shall be non-refundable when made, subject to a default by Seller, but the Additional Deposit shall be applicable to the Purchase Price.

name: Carport Solar
notes:
Hey Michael,

Following our brief discussion about the carports, I wanted to share an ideahas anyone explored installing solar panels on them through an Energy Service Agreement (ESA)? If not, Id be happy to look into the feasibility and model potential returns.

An ESA wouldnt require any upfront capital investment. The provider covers the cost of equipment and installation, and in return, charges a rate thats typically 10-40% lower than local electricity costs. This could be a creative way to reduce house meter expenses while also lowering electricity costs for vacant units, which often add up over time.

Would you be open to me researching this further? Also, do you have an estimate of how much the properties currently spend on house meter electricity and vacant unit utilities each month or annually? That information would help assess the potential savings.

Looking forward to your thoughts.

notes:

Items to Consider
Building Pumps:
    Cost of Smaller Fire Pumps at each building (Swanson)
    Cost of Smaller Domestic Pumps at each building (I think Chase has a number on this)
    Increase in size of pump room: I think this would be minimal, prob need to consider cost of double door but not much more past that.

Site Pump:
    Pump house cost: use numbers from crosspointe
    Cost of Single Fire Pump: use number from crosspointe
    Cost of single domestic pump: use number from crosspointe
    Cost of second water line: will need takeoff from DD set and apply number, if we have site work contractor contact for Greenville then you can get rough cost per linear foot number from them.
